'''Frank Aaen''' (born 25 July 1951 in [[Nørresundby]]) is a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[economist]] and [[Member of Parliament]] (the [[Folketing]]) for [[Enhedslisten]]. On 15 March 2006, he suffered a [[thrombosis]],<ref>Ravn Dorthe (2006-03-15) [http://www.berlingske.dk/article/20060315/danmark/103150312/ ''Frank Aaen ramt af blodprop''] {{da icon}}. ''[[Berlingske|Berlingske Tidende]]''.</ref> but was back in the Folketing by April. He has been a member of parliament from 1994 to 2001 and 2005 to the present. Frank Aaen is an educated economist and holds a master's degree in economics from [[Aalborg University]] which he received in 1985.

